  "prompt": "What is a Founding Father?",
  "response": "A Founding Father is a term used to refer to the group of individuals who played a pivotal role in the establishment and formation of the United States of America. These individuals were key contributors to the American Revolution, the creation of the Declaration of Independence, and the framing of the United States Constitution. Some well-known Founding Fathers include George Washington, Thomas Jefferson, Benjamin Franklin, John Adams, James Madison, and Alexander Hamilton, among others. Their collective efforts helped shape the early government and set the foundation for the country's future development.",
